<br>
For instance, map a kick key to include pressing your epic in button two and you really have to put your epic on button two in every single button page.  Also, if you map your special attack to include the epic and you get an SOV buff, you get a red non-stacking message every kick.  Same thing for mapping forage and sense heading (two others that people like to double up).  I dislike all the random spam it generates, especially sense-heading (easy enough to spend 5 minutes max'ing it each level and then leave it be). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braellarth>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 629<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/5/03 4:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i map it to /corpse key</span><hr size=1> I have sence heading on same key that does /corpse.<br>
